+# ADR-0002 — Three parallel-isolatable pure-utility modules in `src/lib`
+
+- **Status:** Accepted (implemented)
+- **Date:** 2026-05-27
+- **Relates to:** ADR-0001 (test harness + pure-logic coverage — supplies the runner this ADR reuses)
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib` already holds small, dependency-free pure helpers (`cn.ts`, `format.ts`).
+The request adds three more utilities, deliberately specified so that each lives in
+its own file with its own colocated test file and **imports none of the others** —
+making them safe to implement in parallel worktrees and merge with zero conflicts.
+
+Stack: Next.js 16 / React 19 / TypeScript strict, ESM (`"type": "module"`),
+`moduleResolution: bundler`, `noUnusedLocals`/`noUnusedParameters` on. Node v24.
+
+The only shared surface across the three tasks is `package.json` test wiring — a
+one-time edit owned by ADR-0001, not a per-module dependency.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add three file-disjoint modules to `src/lib`, each with a colocated `*.test.ts`:
+
+1. **`slug.ts` — `slugify(text)`**: lowercase → trim → collapse `[^a-z0-9]+` into a
+   single `-` → strip leading/trailing `-`. **ASCII-only by design**: diacritics and
+   non-Latin chars become separators (`Café déjà vu` → `caf-d-j-vu`). Transliteration
+   (`café → cafe`) is explicitly out of scope; raise a new task if SEO needs it.
+2. **`num.ts` — `clamp(value, min, max)` + `roundTo(value, decimals)`**:
+   - `clamp`: inclusive; `±Infinity` value snaps to the nearer bound; `NaN` value
+     propagates as `NaN`; invalid bounds (`min > max` or a non-finite bound) throw
+     `RangeError` — a bad range is a programming error, not data.
+   - `roundTo`: exponential re-parse beats binary-float error (`roundTo(1.005,2) === 1.01`);
+     non-finite value returned unchanged; non-finite/negative `decimals` → 0.
+3. **`str.ts` — `truncate(text, max, ellipsis='…')` + `titleCase(text)`**:
+   - `truncate`: ellipsis counted against `max`, so result length ≤ `max`; within-budget
+     text unchanged; `max ≤ ellipsis.length` → prefix of the ellipsis.
+   - `titleCase`: first char of each word up, rest down; **original whitespace runs
+     preserved** (`"hello   world"` → `"Hello   World"`).
+
+Runner = ADR-0001's harness: `node --import tsx --test "src/**/*.test.ts"`. Tests use
+**extensionless** relative imports (`./slug`, not `./slug.ts`) to satisfy strict `tsc`
+(avoids TS5097) while running fine under the `tsx` loader.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- +24 tests for these three modules; no new framework surface beyond the single `tsx`
+  devDependency (already wired by ADR-0001).
+- The disjoint design is proven: parallel implement/merge is conflict-free outside the
+  one shared `package.json` edit.
+- ASCII-only `slugify` degrades non-Latin input to separators — acceptable for current
+  Latin-script SEO targets; transliteration is a deferred follow-up.
+- Pure internal utilities: no rendered-UI or external-contract change, so no approval
+  gate is required.
+
+## Verification (this run, 2026-05-27)
+
+- Workspace had reset to baseline (`src/lib` held only `cn.ts` + `format.ts`; no `test`
+  script; ADR-0001's test files absent). Re-implemented from this settled decision.
+- `npm test` → **24 pass / 0 fail** (~257 ms, Node v24.12.0).
+- `tsc --noEmit` → clean.
